Lenny Schultz https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lenny_Schultz 0 Lenny Schultz (born December 13, 1933) was a popular comedian during the 1970s on television and at comedy clubs in New York City. His madcap style of improvisational comedy influenced other comedians such as Gallagher, Carrot Top, and David Letterman.
